  \begin {tikzcd}
    p\ar [r, "\pi _b"]\ar [d, "\pi _c"'] & b\ar [d, "f"] \\
    c\ar [r, "g"'] & a
  \end {tikzcd}


 in an abelian category is a pullback if and only if
0\to  p\xrightarrow {(\pi _b, \pi _c)} b\oplus  c\xrightarrow {(f, -g)}a
is exact.

Let x\xrightarrow {f} y be a map in a preabelian category. Then the
following are equivalent:

f is a monomorphism;

f has trivial kernel;

f has coimage x;

0\to  x\xrightarrow {f} y is exact.

Dually, the following are equivalent:

f is an epimorphism;

f has image y;

f has trivial cokernel;

x\xrightarrow {f} y\to  0 is exact.

More precisely, for each n, there is a canonical diagram 




